HEADWORD: Ceratospongiæ
<hw>Cer`a*to*spon"gi*⟦ae⟧</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>ke`ras</grk>, <grk>ke`ratos</grk> horn + <?/
sponge.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of sponges in which the
skeleton consists of horny fibers. It includes all the commercial
sponges.</def>⟦br⟧
